1
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:12,267
<i>Wait a minute, wait a minute,
Miss. Just a moment.</i>

2
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,833
<i>I'm not a pervert.
We're in the men's comfort room.</i>

3
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:17,300
<i>By the way, I'm Jared,
CEO of Add2Cart.</i>

4
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:20,200
<i>Forgive me, okay?
Don't disqualify me.</i>

5
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,267
<i>But on one condition,
let's have coffee later.</i>

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,200
<i> You can't say no.</i>

7
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,500
<i> This is Donabel Custodio.</i>

8
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:27,533
<i> She's Okoy's top money maker.</i>

9
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:31,300
<i>Turns out he did the right
thing, but Okoy did a lousy job.</i>

10
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:34,400
<i>Cecilia told me that the police
still suspect</i>

11
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:35,933
<i>that the person
who killed Donabel</i>

12
00:00:36,067 --> 00:00:37,367
<i>was someone inside
the beauty pageant.</i>

13
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>Mention that to Okoy.
He already know what to do.</i>

14
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>And now, for our last candidate</i>

15
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,900
<i>to complete the Miss Calabari
2025 list...</i>

16
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:47,667
<i> Bobby Enriquez!</i>

17
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:53,600
<i>Why would two police officers
want to join a beauty pageant?</i>

18
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:54,800
<i> They have other agendas.</i>

19
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:56,167
<i> Bobby,</i>

20
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,367
<i>remember what we talked about
earlier in the comfort room,</i>

21
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:58,533
<i>that will push through, okay?
Let's have coffee.</i>

22
00:00:58,667 --> 00:00:59,333
<i> That's not possible.</i>

23
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:00,633
<i> What's that, Bro?</i>

24
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:03,433
<i>Me, I can't come later because
I have something to do.</i>

25
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:06,233
<i>It's okay, Sir.
You're not the one being asked.</i>

26
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:07,000
<i> It's me.</i>

27
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:08,167
<i> Don't be jealous.</i>

28
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:09,567
<i>You and Bobby are not a couple,
right?</i>

29
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:11,933
<i>I'm not jealous.
That's not my style.</i>

30
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:13,200
<i> I came here for work.</i>

31
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,067
<i> Whatever you say. Take care.</i>

32
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:17,867
Abdul!

33
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,167
- What?
- Any update?

34
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:21,867
Friend, there's no update yet.
Just wait there.

35
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,300
What kind of pageant is this?

36
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:25,267
It doesn't even have
a livestream!

37
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,000
Don't be too excited.

38
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:28,167
Just wait a little longer.

39
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,867
What's taking them so long?

40
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,300
My God.

41
00:01:32,433 --> 00:01:33,200
Friend.

42
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,800
- Looks like Bobby's not here.
- What happened?

43
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:46,833
Bobby's not here...

44
00:01:46,967 --> 00:01:48,133
Oh! There she is!

45
00:01:48,267 --> 00:01:49,167
So, Bobby...

46
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,800
How was it? Are you in?

47
00:01:58,867 --> 00:02:02,533
- Congrats! Congrats, Bobby!
- Oh, come on.

48
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:04,467
- I told you. It's true.
- You know, it's a good thing...

49
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,833
that we taught you how to answer
in the Q and A portion.

50
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,633
Of course, we are the reason
why you got in.

51
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:09,300
- Oh my, stop it!
- Yes!

52
00:02:09,433 --> 00:02:10,633
My feet hurt so much!

53
00:02:10,767 --> 00:02:13,300
You know, we really taught you
well for the Q and A portion!

54
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:16,133
- Was I good?
- Yes, right?

55
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:20,800
Hey! Charlie, Peach, and Apple,
they got in too.

56
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:23,633
Oh, those witches.

57
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:26,233
Especially Apple and Peach,

58
00:02:26,367 --> 00:02:27,100
I'll never forget them.

59
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:28,600
Because of them,
we got locked up!

60
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:29,800
That's true!

61
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:31,900
Oh my, when I see them,
they're going to get it from me!

62
00:02:32,033 --> 00:02:33,233
I'll make their heads spin like
a washing machine!

63
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:35,167
I'll make them face
their nightmare.

64
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:37,533
- True!
- Hey! Let them be!

65
00:02:37,667 --> 00:02:38,400
I'm so pissed.

66
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:40,400
Besides, what they did
was right.

67
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:42,300
You guys got out, right?

68
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,900
In fairness, she's right.

69
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:46,833
Anyways, Bobby, you got in.

70
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,367
You should win.

71
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:50,700
Besides, look at the other
contestants,

72
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:51,667
they're all so thin.

73
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,500
Go on a diet and exercise.
Oh, my God!

74
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:55,133
Why? What do you mean?

75
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:58,033
My point is, you're also thin.

76
00:02:58,167 --> 00:03:01,200
If you want, we'll join you
to exercise and diet.

77
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:02,267
- Coming from you? Really?
- Yes.

78
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,333
So that you'll look good
in the gown

79
00:03:04,467 --> 00:03:07,133
and in the swimsuit competition,
right?

80
00:03:07,267 --> 00:03:09,733
And you should practice
wearing your heels.

81
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:10,967
- That's true.
- Yes.

82
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:11,867
Yeah.

83
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,633
Tomorrow, we have catwalk
training

84
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:18,400
and the swimsuit fitting.

85
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:19,667
Oh!

86
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:23,067
Swimsuit fitting, Friend!
Let's buy you some new makeup!

87
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,433
Let's use your 10 million!

88
00:03:25,567 --> 00:03:26,833
That's too much!

89
00:03:26,967 --> 00:03:27,633
Size 11.

90
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:28,167
Size 9.

91
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,300
Hey, you two, stop.

92
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:32,600
That money is allocated
for grandmother.

93
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:33,733
And for us?

94
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:37,000
Besides, I don't need that.
Bag, shoes, makeup?

95
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:38,267
No need.

96
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,267
That's not what I came here for.

97
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,933
I'm here to investigate

98
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:45,900
and catch the person
we're looking for.

99
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:48,467
It's your fault.
You're so greedy.

100
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:51,367
Oh my, what time is it?

101
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,767
Let's go, Captain Isang
might be looking for us.

102
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,100
- Let's go home.
- Yes, let's go.

103
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:57,767
No, you two go ahead.
I have somewhere else to go.

104
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,667
Why?

105
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,967
What's up?

106
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,300
I'm going to meet Jared.

107
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:04,967
Jared?

108
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:05,900
Who's that?

109
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,100
Who's that?

110
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:09,167
Bobby, you already replaced
Tonyo with someone else?

111
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,167
Oh my, I'll tell Tonyo about it.

112
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,433
No, I'll tell him about it.

113
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:15,133
Stop it. Just go see
grandmother.

114
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:16,933
I'll go ahead too. Bye.

115
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,300
Bobby!

116
00:04:20,533 --> 00:04:23,033
What is it again?

117
00:04:23,167 --> 00:04:26,033
Bobby, you're going on a date
wearing your slippers?

118
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:30,267
Oh my, that's right.

119
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:32,633
Girl, will you dance
the tinikling?

120
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:33,433
Annoying.

121
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:36,633
- Oh, my God.
- I hope you're okay.

122
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:39,567
Bobby, who's that Jared guy?

123
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:42,433
Yes, you already replaced
Sir Tonyo with someone else.

124
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:43,333
He's right.

125
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:44,233
Do you know
the three-month rule?

126
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,367
Hey!

127
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,167
Right? And besides,
if you don't want Tonyo anymore,

128
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,433
just give him to us.
Poor thing.

129
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:52,500
Oh my, stop it!
That's not a date!

130
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,000
So go ahead, go see grandmother.
I'm leaving.

131
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,233
- She's going on a date.
- She said it wasn't a date.

132
00:04:58,367 --> 00:05:00,700
- Who is that Jared?
- What does he look like?

133
00:05:28,767 --> 00:05:32,000
Come on, Sir! Ma'am!
Come on, let's eat!

134
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:35,100
My BFFs got in Miss Calabari.

135
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:36,033
Come on, let's go.

136
00:05:36,167 --> 00:05:38,567
There, there's a lot of them.

137
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,000
Here.

138
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,800
Hey, where's Apple?

139
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:45,000
Sis, she was in a hurry
to leave.

140
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,600
I don't know.
I think she has a date again.

141
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:50,467
Wait, Sis, what's up?

142
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,400
Why are you treating them
to food here at the precinct

143
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:53,467
when you can do it at home?

144
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:56,400
So we can share our blessings...

145
00:05:56,533 --> 00:05:57,500
What's going on?

146
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:00,767
Selena...

147
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,633
what's going on?

148
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:07,033
I just wanted to treat you all

149
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:12,167
because my friends
got into Miss Calabari.

150
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:12,900
Do you want some?

151
00:06:13,733 --> 00:06:14,900
Okay, thank you.

152
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:17,633
Thank you.

153
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,567
Spring rolls, my favorite.

154
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:23,233
What's going on here?

155
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:26,167
Lieutenant Samson.

156
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:27,700
Congratulations to you, too.

157
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:30,533
You got into Miss Calabari.

158
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:31,867
And you're even wondering why.

159
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,633
And so did Ma'am Bobby.

160
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:37,067
Wait, where's Ma'am Bobby?

161
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,233
What's with you, Noble?
Aren't you wondering yet?

162
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,567
Bobby's not here.

163
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:44,400
Tonyo's not here.

164
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:48,733
Well then, most likely
they're just bonding, talking.

165
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:52,033
- Bonding, just bonding.
- Bonding.

166
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:55,133
It doesn't seem like Tonyo
is Bobby's bonding partner.

167
00:06:55,267 --> 00:06:56,367
I think it's someone else.

168
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:00,200
Hey, Lieutenant Samson.

169
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:04,500
I know Tonyo very well.

170
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:12,100
That guy has no sense
of jealousy in his body.

171
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:13,000
We can even make a bet.

172
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,133
I'm willing to cut
my finger off.

173
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:19,267
Ma'am Charlie, let's eat.

174
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,600
Come on, the spring rolls
are delicious.

175
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,667
Okay.

176
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,400
Ma'am, go ahead.

177
00:07:27,533 --> 00:07:28,600
That's delicious.

178
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:32,567
- Sir, your order.
- Thank you, thank you.

179
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,733
Sir Jared.

180
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:38,033
Sit down, sit down.

181
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:40,767
Thank you.

182
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,533
Bobby, I'm sorry.

183
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:46,633
I already ordered something
for us.

184
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:49,733
I heard their coffee here
is really good,

185
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:51,800
especially when you pair it
with a cinnamon roll.

186
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:57,167
<i>Bro, cinnamon roll is Bobby's
least favorite bread!</i>

187
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:59,467
<i>You're going
to be embarrassed now.</i>

188
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,000
Well, that's okay.

189
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:04,633
You know, cinnamon roll
is my favorite.

190
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:06,400
That's delicious,
especially with coffee.

191
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:08,333
Yes, that's right.

192
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:10,100
Favorite?

193
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:12,733
<i>You said earlier that
you don't like cinnamon roll.</i>

194
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,933
<i>You're full of lies, too, Bobby.</i>

195
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:16,900
There you go.

196
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:19,633
Hi, Ma'am, Sir.

197
00:08:21,367 --> 00:08:22,333
Nice!

198
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:23,267
Thank you.

199
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,733
That's it, Sir,
the order is complete.

200
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:28,767
- Thank you, Ma'am.
- Thank you, thank you.

201
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,167
- Shall we try it?
- Okay.

202
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:36,400
It's so delicious.

203
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:38,267
This is what I like
about cinnamon roll,

204
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:42,667
classic, not too sweet,
very comforting.

205
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,800
It's like...

206
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:46,100
It's like someone's hugging you,
something like that.

207
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:47,133
You're right.

208
00:08:47,267 --> 00:08:48,800
<i>Then let your grandmother
hug you.</i>

209
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:51,000
<i>You even used cinnamon roll
as an excuse.</i>

210
00:08:51,133 --> 00:08:52,400
<i> I'm sure you're a pervert.</i>

211
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:54,700
Sir, are you going to order now?

212
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,533
You've been there
for a while now.

213
00:08:58,667 --> 00:08:59,867
Are you going to order now?

214
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,567
Lieutenant Conde?

215
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:09,200
Bobby?

216
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,500
Bobby?

217
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:14,167
Bobby!

218
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,867
I didn't know you're here too.
Wow, what a small world.

219
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,500
I won't order anymore
because I'm about to leave now.

220
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:22,000
- Okay, Sir. Okay.
- Thank you!

221
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:25,100
Bobby, I'll go ahead, okay?

222
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:35,067
Sir Jared, just a moment, okay?
I'll just go somewhere.

223
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,567
I'll be right back.

224
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,533
Sorry.

225
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,433
Lieutenant Conde!

226
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:52,367
What are you doing here?
Are you stalking me?

227
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,767
Of course not!

228
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,833
I didn't even know that
you're going there.

229
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:58,233
What do you mean?

230
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:02,133
Weren't you there when Sir Jared
invited me for coffee here?

231
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:06,100
What? You're going to deny it?
You're so fussy!

232
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:07,067
You really thought...

233
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,800
When you saw me earlier
you even said,

234
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:13,533
"Bobby? Is that you?
What a small world!"

235
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:16,667
Pretending not to know, huh?
You're so amazing.

236
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,333
You could win an award.

237
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:21,267
Okay, fine.

238
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,600
- I'm following you because...
- There you go.

239
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:24,967
I'm worried.

240
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,833
What if he's the killer
we're looking for?

241
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:30,167
Maybe he already know
that you're a cop.

242
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:33,600
How many times do I have
to tell you that I can manage?

243
00:10:35,267 --> 00:10:37,133
Be careful, Bobby.

244
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:39,567
He might be studying you.

245
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:42,067
Maybe his being a good boy
is just for show.

246
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,500
And you'll give in right away.

247
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:45,900
Give in right away?

248
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:48,133
- What do you mean?
- Isn't it true?

249
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:50,433
Suddenly, the cinnamon roll
has become your favorite

250
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:52,667
when you just said earlier
that you don't eat that.

251
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,567
There you go.

252
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:55,233
The truth finally came out,

253
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:57,400
that the cinnamon roll
was your issue.

254
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,967
Bobby, you don't know him.

255
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,600
You don't know him either.

256
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:06,600
Well, if he's really the one
we're looking for,

257
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:08,900
it would be better
if I get close to him

258
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:11,033
so we could get some evidence,
right?

259
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:16,900
- Bobby...
- Bobby, your face!

260
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:19,167
You even say "small
world, small world."

261
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:22,233
You really thought
I couldn't see you?

262
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,067
What?

263
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,267
Well, the truth has finally
come out!

264
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:33,067
That Bobby is really
after the money!

265
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:38,167
Okay, Attorney. Just update me.

266
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,400
Madame!

267
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:46,000
I have news for you.

268
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:48,967
Please, I'm not in the mood!

269
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:51,933
Madame, you're in a bad mood
right away?

270
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:55,367
Fine, tell me about it
so you can let it out.

271
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,800
Relax!

272
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,700
It's Bobby.

273
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:03,567
She already got money
from Joaquin's inheritance.

274
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:06,767
She's really shameless!

275
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:10,500
Madame, I think I know where
she's going to use the money,

276
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:14,133
and it's connected to my news.

277
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,933
I just found out

278
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:19,867
that Bobby is going to join
Miss Calabari.

279
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:26,267
The nerve of that bastard!

280
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,700
She really thinks she's special.

281
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,633
I know, right, Madame.

282
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:37,100
But aren't you one of the judges
of Miss Calabari?

283
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:39,033
You already know what to do.

284
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:39,867
No.

285
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,167
I want to do something now.

286
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:48,233
Hello, Francis.

287
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,533
This is Sofia Guerrero. Yes.

288
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:54,367
I just want to know,

289
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:58,067
what are the upcoming events
on Miss Calabari?

290
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:08,933
It's good that Samson
and Enriquez made it

291
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:10,867
to Miss Calabari, right?

292
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,867
Yeah, so did Selena's
two friends.

293
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,100
They went to the office
and treated us to snacks.

294
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:20,000
Too bad, you didn't make it.
Where were you?

295
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,500
I was just investigating a case,

296
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:25,067
so I couldn't get back
to the station right away.

297
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,867
Investigating a case? Why?

298
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,700
Did you get a new lead
on Donabel's case?

299
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:31,833
Nothing yet, Bok.

300
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:34,867
This is a different case
I'm investigating.

301
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:40,067
There's a guy who's going
behind my back.

302
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,200
What's that, Bok?

303
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,233
No, nothing, nothing.

304
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:47,100
Any update from the station?

305
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:49,400
Well, chief's coming in
tomorrow.

306
00:13:49,533 --> 00:13:51,533
He can't seem to relax
on his vacation.

307
00:13:51,667 --> 00:13:53,600
He's excited to get back
to work.

308
00:13:53,733 --> 00:13:58,600
Bok, Samson said earlier
that Enriquez is hanging out

309
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:00,333
with a different guy.

310
00:14:00,467 --> 00:14:03,300
Of course, I defended you.
I said...

311
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:10,533
I'm 100% sure that Conde
isn't the jealous type.

312
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:12,233
It's a good thing
that I defended you.

313
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:15,333
Because their swimsuit training
is tomorrow.

314
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:17,567
I'm sure there'll be a lot
of people watching.

315
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:26,967
What is his problem?

316
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:41,533
Hi.

317
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,433
Your jacket looks nice,
isn't it?

318
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:47,000
Where did you buy that?

319
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:50,867
Ma'am, this is only
for the staff and organizers.

320
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:56,700
Do you have a list of names
of those who have it?

321
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:59,933
No, Ma'am. It's just really
for the staff.

322
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:02,033
Okay, it's just for the staff.

323
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,000
Looks nice. I want one too.

324
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:07,200
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

325
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,533
Please sign here first, Ma'am.

326
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,900
- Bobby!
- Thank you.

327
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:15,367
- Bobby!
- Teresa.

328
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,067
Bobby, how are you?

329
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,367
I'm okay.

330
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,800
You know, it's a good thing
that I know a candidate here.

331
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:25,433
Because those other women
are snobbish.

332
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:28,033
Just stay close to me.

333
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,733
Okay. Come on, let's sit down!

334
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:33,133
Wait a minute, I'll just go
to the comfort room.

335
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:35,033
We're not going to start yet,
right?

336
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,333
Not yet, but I'll just save you
a seat.

337
00:15:37,467 --> 00:15:39,767
Okay, thanks.
I'll just go to you later.

338
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:40,733
Okay.

339
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:46,600
Jared Lopez...

340
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,433
He doesn't have any social media
accounts?

341
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:08,067
<i>That's Jared Lopez,
CEO of Add2Cart.</i>

342
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,467
Add2Cart.

343
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:13,867
Add2Cart...

344
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:18,933
Contact number.

345
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:28,500
Hello?

346
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:33,167
Can you please connect me
to the office of the CEO?

347
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:39,633
I would like to follow up on
our meeting about our product.

348
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:40,833
I'm sorry.

349
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,267
Mr. Lee is out of the country
right now.

350
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,733
May I get your name?

351
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,033
Mr. Lee?

352
00:16:48,167 --> 00:16:49,200
No, no.

353
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:52,000
I want the CEO.

354
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:53,167
Yes, Sir.

355
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:57,233
Mr. Ronald Lee. He's out
of the country for a conference.

356
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:09,133
Jared Lopez is not the CEO
of Add2Cart.

357
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,167
Bobby.

358
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:23,233
Hi, Sir Jared.

359
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:24,933
What are your activities today?

360
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:28,900
Today, we have catwalk training.

361
00:17:29,033 --> 00:17:30,300
I don't know what that's like.

362
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:31,467
Catwalk training?

363
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,600
You'll enjoy that.
You can do that.

364
00:17:33,733 --> 00:17:35,400
- Hi, Ma'am Bobby!
- Hey!

365
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,767
Apple, Peach, this is Sir Jared.

366
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,700
Sir Jared, this is Apple
and Peach.

367
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,233
- Apple, by the way.
- Nice to meet you.

368
00:17:42,367 --> 00:17:44,867
- Hello, Sir Jared. I'm Peach.
- Nice to meet you.

369
00:17:46,067 --> 00:17:49,067
So, I'll go ahead. Good luck.

370
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:50,733
- Okay, thank you, Sir.
- I'll go ahead.

371
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:51,933
- Thank you.
- Bye.

372
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,833
Ma'am Bobby, who's that?

373
00:17:55,967 --> 00:17:57,933
Why are you with him,
Ma'am Bobby?

374
00:17:58,067 --> 00:17:59,000
That's Sir Jared,

375
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:02,033
he's our major sponsor here
at Miss Calabari.

376
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:03,333
Really?

377
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,900
So, can we ask you
for his number?

378
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:07,533
- I'll go first.
- Me first, Ma'am Bobby.

379
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:09,133
- You two, really.
- Me first.

380
00:18:09,267 --> 00:18:10,500
- He's cute.
- I don't have a boyfriend.

381
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:12,633
- He's so cute.
- I've been single for years.

382
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:14,767
What's with you?
You're so noisy!

383
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,433
It's embarrassing
for the people here.

384
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:19,300
Our librarian is here.

385
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:20,933
Ma'am, hello.

386
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:22,800
- Hello, Ma'am.
- Sorry.

387
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:26,633
- Sorry.
- Bobby, it's about to start.

388
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:27,533
- It's starting already?
- Yes.

389
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:28,300
Okay.

390
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:30,600
Ma'am, it's starting already.

391
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:32,233
- Let's go, Ma'am.
- I don't know about you!

392
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,900
- Come on.
- You're so noisy.

393
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:36,800
Welcome back, beautiful ladies
of Calabari.

394
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:39,600
So, for today's catwalk
training,

395
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:41,833
we have a very special guest.

396
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:44,800
She is a former Miss Calabari
crown holder.

397
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:46,767
And do you know
how lucky you are?

398
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:50,500
Because this person
is very busy, but she's here.

399
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:51,667
So, ladies,

400
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:55,700
let's all welcome the stunning,
Mrs. Sophia Guerrero.

401
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:03,467
Hello, everyone.
Please, take your seats.

402
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,333
Let's say it together!

403
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,233
Long live the chief!

404
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:26,400
Long live!

405
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:27,533
Seriously, Garcia.

406
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:29,500
You're full of foolishness,
I just came back.

407
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:32,433
Chief, we're just happy
you're back.

408
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:33,400
Welcome back.

409
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:34,833
Thank you, Garcia.

410
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:40,567
- Long live!
- Chief, welcome back.

411
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,600
Conde, thank you very much.

412
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:48,500
I know our morale
is low right now

413
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:51,000
because of what happened
to Lieutenant Robles,

414
00:19:51,133 --> 00:19:55,300
but I believe we can bounce
back from this.

415
00:19:55,433 --> 00:19:57,933
So let's do our jobs well

416
00:19:58,067 --> 00:20:01,367
to restore the trust
of our countrymen.

417
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,233
Is that clear?

418
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,000
Sir, yes, Sir!

419
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,467
Okay, back to work!

420
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:09,467
Major Flores.

421
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:10,333
Mayor.

422
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:11,267
Welcome back.

423
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,600
Thank you, Mayor.

424
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:13,733
Can we talk?

425
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:14,700
Sure, Mayor.

426
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:17,133
Torres, prepare a cup of coffee
for Mayor.

427
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:18,700
Yes, Sir.

428
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,033
Let's go here, Mayor.

429
00:20:22,667 --> 00:20:23,667
Sit down, Mayor.

430
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:26,033
Thank you, Major.

431
00:20:27,967 --> 00:20:29,433
Mayor, what's up?

432
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:34,200
Major, I know these past
few weeks,

433
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,800
Calabari has been through a lot.

434
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:39,267
The crime doesn't seem to stop.

435
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:40,100
Mayor...

436
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:43,867
we're doing everything we can.

437
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,500
I know,

438
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:48,900
and I want to thank you for the
dedication shown by Station 12.

439
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:50,967
So if your precinct needs
anything else,

440
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,400
just let me know, okay?

441
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:54,033
We're ready to help.

442
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:55,633
Thank you very much, Mayor.

443
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:57,967
By the way, Major...

444
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:00,100
I don't know if you've heard,

445
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:04,167
there's an upcoming Miss
Calabari beauty pageant.

446
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,500
Yes, Mayor.

447
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:10,500
I assure you that the outcome
of this event will be smooth.

448
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:12,400
Okay, it should be.

449
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:16,933
We have many sponsors coming
from other provinces.

450
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,633
We also have visitors
from other places.

451
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:23,800
I want them to have a memorable
time for tourism.

452
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:27,333
And like what Amo said,
for Calabari.

453
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:29,400
Yes, Mayor.

454
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:30,800
You can count on it.

455
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:36,300
Speaking of,
the beauty pageant...

456
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,767
I saw Bobby made it
to that beauty pageant.

457
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,767
It's good that she still has
time to be a police officer.

458
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,933
It seems like she wants
to take a break.

459
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:47,667
It seems like she wants
to resign for the meantime.

460
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,367
Why?

461
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,333
Because, Mayor,
her grandmother is sick.

462
00:21:52,467 --> 00:21:53,700
She wants to take care of her.

463
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,033
I understand.

464
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:58,400
Excuse me, Major.

465
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:00,900
The coffee and snacks
are already in your office.

466
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:02,300
Thank you, Torres.

467
00:22:02,433 --> 00:22:03,700
Let's go, Mayor!

468
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:04,767
Thank you.

469
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,667
This way.

470
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,200
All right, ladies.

471
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,400
Let's start this catwalk
training.

472
00:22:17,533 --> 00:22:20,700
I just want to see
what you all have.

473
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:22,367
Any volunteers?

474
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:33,267
Miss Bobby Enriquez.

475
00:22:34,433 --> 00:22:36,567
Ma'am, I didn't raise my hand.

476
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:38,300
That's okay. Stand up.

477
00:22:38,433 --> 00:22:39,567
Come on, stand up,

478
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:43,200
and please show us
your best walk.

479
00:22:49,667 --> 00:22:50,733
Go, Bobby.

480
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:04,167
Stop right there.

481
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:07,300
That's the walk of a loser.

482
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:12,200
Her face alone looks so sour.

483
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:18,000
It's like you didn't get a lot
of money from my husband.

484
00:23:47,633 --> 00:23:51,133
I really hate that girl.
She's too much of a star.

485
00:23:51,267 --> 00:23:55,400
Do you want me to eliminate her
in the first round?

486
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:56,667
Is that possible?

487
00:23:56,800 --> 00:24:01,000
If you think you're good
at modeling and catwalking,

488
00:24:01,133 --> 00:24:03,400
you'll do the catwalk
in your swimsuits

489
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:08,500
until I see the confidence
that the judges want to see.

490
00:24:08,633 --> 00:24:10,733
Haven't you talked to someone
from Add2Cart?

491
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:14,033
They already told you that Jared
isn't the CEO, right?

492
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:15,000
That's the thing.

493
00:24:15,133 --> 00:24:16,367
So if he's really a fake,

494
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:19,167
how did he bring up the name
of Add2Cart to Miss Calabari

495
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:20,733
if that's a public event?

496
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:21,800
Hello.

497
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:23,133
There were two police officers
here earlier,

498
00:24:23,267 --> 00:24:24,700
asking about you.

499
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:27,000
I'll be careful.
No one will know the truth.
